      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Mechanical tension and metabolic stress are two key drivers for muscle hypertrophy, but they work in different ways. Mechanical tension, the muscle's ability to handle heavy loads and resist force, is the primary signal for building muscle fibers. In contrast, metabolic stress is the accumulation of byproducts like lactate during intense, high-rep sets, which creates a cellular environment that signals for growth. A good hypertrophy program needs a balance of both, though you can lean into one or the other depending on your training style.",
      "source": "target",
